        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 13 at 4:08PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 408 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Chaco Canyon, or 31 miles north of Crownpoint, moving north
northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Chaco Canyon and Nageezi.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
